{
  "texts": [
    "The breadth of guidelines is classified as general or subject-specific depending on target research areas mentioned in the guideline.",
    "In terms of the consensus process, comprehensive guidelines are based on a structured, consensus-based, methodical development approach involving multiple experts and relevant stakeholders with details on the exact protocol.",
    "Collaborative guidelines are (presumably) developed using a formal consensus procedure involving multiple experts, but provide no details on the exact protocol or methodological structure.",
    "Expert-led guidelines are not developed through a consensusbased procedure, do not involve relevant stakeholders, or do not clearly describe the development procedure.",
    "include in this systematic review."
  ]
}